abstract: Stocks rallied despite uncertainty, suggesting investor optimism, in part because of acceleration of the sustained fall in energy prices.
snippet: Stocks rallied despite uncertainty, suggesting investor optimism, in part because of acceleration of the sustained fall in energy prices.
lead_paragraph: UNCERTAINTY is usually bad news in business, and there was plenty of uncertainty this week. But stocks rallied nonetheless, suggesting investor optimism, in part because of acceleration of the sustained fall in energy prices.

headline.main: A Lot of Uncertainty, Except on Wall Street
